489,2023-07-12,Transfund Data Analyst,OK,"Req ID: 73751
Location: Tulsa -TUL
Areas of Interest: Information Services
Pay Transparency Salary Range: Not Available

BOK Financial (BOKF), Headquartered in Tulsa, Oklahoma, BOK Financial Corporation (NASDAQ: BOKF) is a top 25 U.S.-based financial services holding company with operations in ten states – Oklahoma, Texas, Arkansas, Arizona, Colorado, Kansas/Missouri, New Mexico, Nebraska and Wisconsin. The company began more than 100 years ago in Tulsa and has successfully diversified into a variety of industries, businesses and geographies. .
Bonus Type
Discretionary
Summary
If you are looking for a job that combines a passion for innovation, an opportunity for growth, and a culture of teamwork, then you've come to the right place.

Headquartered in Tulsa, Oklahoma, TransFund, a business unit owned by BOK Financial, and a top-ten ATM network and debit, credit and merchant processor serving financial institutions and companies throughout the U.S. and Virgin Islands. With more than 46 years of experience in the financial services industry, TransFund delivers exceptional payment processing solutions with service, knowledge and consultation, so that clients can differentiate themselves, compete with companies of any size, and profitably expand their business.
Job Description

The TransFund Data Analyst is responsible for providing and maintaining recurring reports and data analyses in support of TransFund management and TransFund customer business needs. Responsible for monitoring and maintaining automated jobs that control the production and dissemination of business reports. Provides administrative support for TransFund’s file transfer environment. Develops strong working relationships with internal TransFund departments and line of business partners to understand the TransFund business model, key performance indicators, strategies and plans
Team Culture

We are committed to building an encouraging, caring, and supportive team environment that fosters personal development and professional growth. We are owners. Every day, we take initiative—with integrity and courage—to make our company and our clients stronger.
How You'll Spend Your Time

In consultation with TransFund senior IT management, you will extract data, typically from a database, perform a broad range of analyses, and employ data visualization tools to convey business learnings based on underlying data.

You will exercise sound judgment in researching problems, evaluating various solutions, and using industry standard analytical methodologies to demonstrate support of data-driven conclusions to management.
You will update and maintain regularly distributed reports for multiple line of business strategic initiatives to inform key business decision made by Division leadership.
You will ensure effective data quality and validation controls are in place to support accurate reporting and mitigation of risk associated with inaccurate or incomplete data.

You will resolve automated report failures by identifying the underlying root cause of the failure and determining and implementing a solution that resolves the failure both immediately, and mitigates or eliminates the risk of future failures.

Working in conjunction with TransFund business leaders and fellow subject matter experts, you will assist with ad hoc report requests supporting all lines of business within TransFund by accessing relevant data sources, querying and summarizing data, and providing reports as needed and with respect to the target audience.

In conjunction with fellow IT members, you will assist with administrating the TransFund file transfer environment by setting up and managing user access to reports and directories where automated reports are distributed.
You will research relevant payment card industries, financial service, and TransFund line of business issues to build upon knowledge base, identifying trends and sharing insights with team.

You will gain a comprehensive understanding of the TransFund data warehouse environment, and will build upon a broad understanding of the underlying technologies used in support of TransFund data operations
column2: such as Oracle Database, Unix shell scripting, SQL, and various BI tools.

column1: You will research and maintain a continued education curriculum related to analytic technology, especially technologies currently in use by TransFund, such as Oracle PL/SQL and R/R Studio.
Education & Experience Requirements

This level of knowledge is normally acquired by completion of a Bachelor’s Degree in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics and 1-2 years of relevant professional business experience and/or the pursuit of a Master’s degree (e.g., MBA, MSF).
Skills

Strong conceptual thinking, analytical, and problem solving skills, including the ability to analyze complex problems that include interrelationships and dependencies in order to identify common themes and solutions
Strong aptitude to collect and analyze information and make appropriate recommendations
Self-motivated, disciplined, and task focused
Strong time management and organizational skills to effectively handle projects in a fast-paced, high-volume, and deadline focused environment
Very highly detail-oriented
Well-developed written and oral communication skills to effectively represent self and the Division, as well as the ability to present complex information and issues in a clear and concise manner
Thorough knowledge writing and utilizing SQL queries
General knowledge of Oracle PL/SQL objects such as procedures and packages
General experience with data aggregation, analysis, and business reporting
General experience with data visualization and report building/automation
Any experience with the R programming language and R Studio helpful
General knowledge of UNIX or similar *nix shell scripting helpful
Working knowledge of BI tools such as Jasper Studio and Microsoft Power BI helpful
Working knowledge of financial services and EFT Networks helpful

BOK Financial is a stable and financially strong organization that provides excellent training and development to support building the long term careers of our employees. With passion, skill and partnership you can make an impact on the success of the bank, our customers and your own career!
Apply today and take the first step towards your next career opportunity!

490,2023-08-05,Lead Data Analyst - Remote | WFH,TX,"Join our dynamic and inclusive team, where growth is not just a goal, but a way of life. Embrace a transformative journey that will empower you to unleash your potential, surrounded by a community of passionate engineers eager to learn, advance, and make a tangible impact every step of the way.
Compensation And Benefits
Enjoy competitive compensation, encompassing base pay and enticing annual incentives.
Embrace comprehensive health, life insurance, and well-being benefits tailored to your location.
Secure your future with robust retirement benefits.
Recharge and rejuvenate with ample Paid Time Off and other leave options.
Embrace our flexible/hybrid work model – work on-site for three dynamic days and choose two days of remote collaboration. (Onsite Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and a third day of your preference)
Why You'll Thrive In This Role

As the IT Investment Management Senior Data Analyst, you'll embark on an exciting journey of unraveling data-driven insights to shape our IT Service strategy and governance. Join a team committed to driving excellence within the IT Investment Management realm, with key responsibilities that include:
Unearth and categorize pivotal data sources across the enterprise through insightful analysis.
Curate, manage, and refine data, orchestrating its seamless transition into a robust database or data warehouse.
Craft intelligent data models, spotlighting essential dimensions and key facts for informed decision-making.
Illuminate data trends and revelations, transforming complex information into captivating insights.
Weave compelling data narratives through visionary dashboards and impactful reports.
Uphold data accuracy and completeness, spearheading quality assurance efforts.
Elevate the data lifecycle through strategic automation collaboration with skilled data engineers.
Foster strong stakeholder relationships, collaborating across the enterprise to bolster data-driven initiatives.
Please note that the scope of responsibilities extends beyond the details outlined above.
Your Skill Set For Success
Leverage your minimum of 6 years of relevant experience.
While a Bachelor's degree is preferred, equivalent experience is equally valued.
Additional Qualities
Craft user-friendly, intuitive data models by harnessing insights from diverse datasets.
Navigate databases and data warehousing tools adeptly, with expertise in platforms like Snowflake.
Engineer captivating dashboards and automated reports using PowerBI and Tableau.
Master intermediate to advanced MS Office skills, with a focus on Excel and PowerPoint proficiency.
Unleash programming prowess, preferably in SQL, JavaScript, Python, or R.
Familiarity with statistical modeling techniques such as Standard Deviation and Regression is a plus.
A grasp of IT Asset Management, IT Portfolio Management, and IT Financial concepts is advantageous.
Gain insight into general IT landscapes, encompassing Application Delivery/Support and Infrastructure Services.
Join us on this transformative adventure and be part of a team committed to redefining what's possible. Let's shape the future, together.

494,2023-08-02,Business Data Analyst: Enterprise AI Services,TX,"HP is the world’s leading personal systems and printing company
column2: we create technology that makes life better for everyone, everywhere. Our innovation comes from small, focused teams of individuals, each collaborating and contributing their own perspectives, knowledge, and experience to advance the way the world works and lives.

column1: Join HP’s core team of platform engineers, technical program managers, and data specialists to elevate a vibrant world-wide software community to its fullest creative, collaborative potential. We are the developer-experience (DevEx) platform-engineering team responsible for investing in and accelerating our multidimensional software community. We work across all dimensions of software R&D at enterprise scale. Together we count as our customers the thousands of developers, data scientists, enterprise architects, and designers who bring to life HP’s products, services, and solutions for millions of users in every country. Our ongoing work is to enable and streamline the services needed most by HP’s developers: your product's users will be your software peers with ambitions ranging from those creating specialized device-level software controlling the electro-mechanical and micro-fluidic magic of life-sciences products, to those building cloud services which support millions of end users all around the globe.

Your role is Business Data Analyst for the new suite of AI-powered developer services for use by a diverse population of software engineers and programmers all around the world. You will support an agile technical team, facilitating insights for how we manage engagement and ongoing community use with our technology offerings, and you will measure your success through the clarity and insights your work brings to the successful leadership and representation of the overall program. In collaboration with HP’s developer community you are a key member of the team focused on world-wide software development practices, maintaining HP’s legacy of quality while helping drive ever more competitive end-customer solutions to market at an industry-leading pace.

The Business Data Analyst candidate we are seeking is ready to apply data aggregation, analysis, summarization, and reporting knowledge and creativity to resolve complex logistical issues within our program’s established guidelines and to comprehensibly describe and recommend appropriate alternatives based on your careful analysis. Sought candidates are hungry to tackle enterprise-scale software community analytics challenges of diverse complexity and scope. Top candidates will have experience in an enterprise context, supporting programs involving diverse technical communities, will have shown prior savvy as the curator of key program data feeds, analysis and reporting, and will be comfortable defining and/or creating data analysis solutions in order to address emerging needs.

As a Business Data Analyst you will apply subject matter knowledge to solve common and complex business issues within established guidelines, and you will recommend appropriate alternatives. You will work on problems of diverse complexity and scope. You may act as a team lead providing direction to team activities and facilitate information validation and team decision making. You will exercise independent judgment within generally defined policies and practices to identify and select a solution.
Responsibilities

Participates as a member of team of other technology professionals carrying out the investigation, design, development, execution, and implementation of data aggregation and summarization projects to generate new business insights and inform technical program direction.
Creates plans, data collection and analysis procedures, and data insight visualizations for assigned projects.
Collaborates with internal and external partners to perform experiments and validations in accordance with overall plan.
Collaborates with SMEs to develop procedures for collecting, recording, analyzing, and communicating data for review and feedback.
Provides guidance and mentoring to less-experienced staff members.
Knowledge & Skills
Using technical design and data collection and aggregation methodologies, tools and analysis packages to collect, validate, and analyze technical and operational data.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Application and implementation of data-processing and summarization designs, procedures and processes, and data analysis.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
column2: mastery in English and local language.

column1: Ability to effectively communicate analysis plans, proposals, and results, and negotiate options at management levels.
Scope & Impact
Collaborates with peers, junior data scientists and engineers, SMEs and external and internal research and product development partners.
Typically interacts with high-level Individual Contributors, Managers and Program Core Teams.
Participates in projects requiring data science engineering.
Education & Experience
Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Economics, Physics, Computer Science, or equivalent technology domain.
Typically 4-6 years’ experience.
HP Offers a Comprehensive Benefits Package, Including
Dental insurance
Disability insurance
Employee assistance program
Flexible schedule
Flexible spending account
Health insurance
Life insurance

HP is a technology company that operates in more than 170 countries around the world united in creating technology that makes life better for everyone, everywhere.

496,2023-07-20,Data Analyst - Administrative Assistant - US Marshals Service,MA,"Job Description

Tuba Group, Inc. is a small federal contracting business and a CMMI® Level 3 Rated, ISO9001:2015 certified organization. with a primary focus in accounting, financial, systems, technical, engineering, administrative, management, and subject matter expertise services accounting and auditing service. Our mission is to provide value-added solutions that contribute to the success of government agencies, small businesses and independent professionals by leveraging the skill and talent our most valuable resources - our people.

Tuba Group is seeking a Data Analyst to deliver excellent support to our client the United States Marshals Service.

Requires: United States Citizenship
Requires: Bachelor's Degree
General Summary
Provide administrative information and assistance concerning case to other investigative agencies, local law enforcement agencies, U.S. Attorney, other DOJ processing units, and higher headquarters.

Extract data from agency data base for management and program report
Provide organization and management of case files

BSD OBG - Lindau Lab - Research
About The Department

The Lindau Laboratory at The University of Chicago is an interdisciplinary, team-based laboratory performing human-level observational, interventional, and health services research motivated by a fundamental concern for the principle of justice in health and health care. The lab, funded predominantly by agencies of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services for more than 15 years, employs about 20 full and part-time researchers and staff across disciplines including epidemiology, gerontology, anthropology, neurobiology, cancer biology, public health, and data science. The lab routinely collaborates across disciplines, departments, and with investigators at other institutions including experts in the fields of computer science, geriatrics, oncology, public health, social services administration, psychology, neuroscience, materials science, engineering and other medical and social science fields. The work of the lab focuses in two main areas: 1) preservation and treatment of female sexual function in the context of aging, cancer and other common diseases and 2) social determinants of health, with a particular concern for women and older adults living in socioeconomically marginalized communities. Our research and programmatic activities include Bionic Breast, WomanLab, Feed1st and CommunityRx. The Lab has spun out two companies: Now Pow, LLC (acquired by Unite Us, LLC in 2021) and MAPS Corps, 501c3, both based in Hyde Park, Chicago, IL. column1: Whistic is committed to growing diversity, equity, inclusion, and belonging across three key dimensions:

About Whistic
Whistic is on a mission to become the Vendor Security Network where buyers and sellers establish and maintain ongoing connections, enabling faster business decisions.

Here’s how it works: When a company is seeking out a vendor that will have access to its sensitive data, that company must assess the vendor to ensure it meets certain information security thresholds. This assessment process results in cumbersome, clunky, and slow spreadsheets emailed back and forth — eating up info security resources and ultimately delaying deals.

That’s where Whistic comes in. Our market-defining platform enables security and sales teams to proactively conduct and respond to third party security assessments by streamlining and automating the process, transforming the work for companies all over the world, saving professionals valuable time, and ultimately helping to safeguard sensitive information.

This vacancy will be filled at one of two levels - Health Data Analyst or Senior Health Data Analyst. Selected applicant will be offered the position that most closely matches their education and experience.
Salary Range
Health Data Analyst: $66,930 – $83,662
Senior Health Data Analyst: $80,985 – $101,231
What You Will Do
Research and Data Analysis
Develops and automates queries in TRS’ data warehouse to extract data for use in spreadsheets, models, dashboards, and summaries that support decision-making.
Reconciles financial performance guarantees relating to medical loss ratios, claim trends, pharmacy rebates and discounts, and ROIs. (Senior)
Reviews and reports on health care claims, participant service utilization, and pricing to assist with HIB management decisions.
Facilitates the interpretation of health care data from external sources including data from TRS' health care consultants, insurance companies, or other industry resources.
Analyzes detailed enrollment, claim, utilization and other health care related data to identify trends and anomalies, and to identify areas of action.
Analyze provider reimbursement levels, high cost claims, costs by geographic area and place of service, and claim accuracy.
Identify enrollment and cost trends, cost-saving opportunities, and potential fraud, waste, and abuse.
Reviews and validates reports on health plan performance.
Analyzes claim data to support invoice processing. (Senior).
Health Care Services Procurement & Contract Management
Works with vendors and external partners to carry out research related to the administration of TRS health plans.
Communicates regularly with vendors to address business needs and service issues.
Reviews and analyzes various routine vendor reports on a monthly, quarterly, and annual basis.
Works with TRS' legal and purchasing departments in the renewal of contracts and amendments.
Assists with evaluating HIB’s business needs related to plan performance and vendor services.
Assists with the evaluation of bidder proposals with respect to operational capabilities and financial terms.
Assists with the development of procurement documents, such as statements of work and evaluation criteria.
Negotiates business and financial terms of contracts with vendors and finalizes contract documents. (Senior)
Program Administration
Researches, recommends, and implements methodologies for reporting health care data and statistics including key performance indicators for program activities.
Regularly communicates with vendors related to plan performance and initiatives, claims and utilization, provider network updates, pharmaceutical changes, marketplace situations and trends.
Assists with the reconciliation of financial performance guarantees relating to medical loss ratios, claim trends, pharmacy rebates and discounts, and ROIs.
Supports other areas of HIB in analyzing program data and developing key performance indicators and dashboards as needed.
Monitor vendor performance in areas of cost trends, service/process quality and delivery, implementation of plan initiatives, and contract compliance.
Review claim and enrollment data to provide support for invoice processing and benefit decision-making.
Participates on special projects, task forces, and committees as needed.
Coordinates and oversees internal and external audits of contractors and resolves audit findings. (Senior)
Addresses and resolves non-compliance or subpar performance issues with contractors. (Senior)
Performs related work as assigned.
Required Education
WHAT YOU WILL BRING:
Bachelor's degree form an accredited college or university in accounting, finance, mathematics, statistics, business, health care administration, or a closely related field.

High school diploma or equivalent and additional health care industry, benefits and/or health insurance claims processing, research, data and/or financial analysis, accounting, auditing or other directly related experience may substitute for the required education on a year-for-year basis.

Advanced degree in actuary science, accounting, finance, mathematics, statistics, business, health care, health care administration, or closely related field may substitute for one year of the required experience.
Required Experience
Three (3) years of full-time experience in analyzing health care claims data or administration of a health insurance plan.
Senior Required Experience
Five (5) years of full-time experience in analyzing health care claims data or administration of a health insurance plan.
Preferred Qualifications
Advanced degree in actuary science, finance, mathematics, statistics, business, health care administrations, or closely related field.
Experience in pharmacy benefits, analyzing pharmacy claims, formularies, or contracts within the last six (6) months.
Knowledge of

Data analysis concepts and methods, including education equivalent to at least statistics for business, health benefit claims processing, Medicare, coordination of benefits, standard medical procedures, and billing.
Health care claims data including CPT, HCPCS, DRG, ICD-10, and NDC.
Health care related laws, regulations, policies and procedures.
Self-funded and fully insured group health benefit products and contracts, including Medicare Advantage.
Provider networks, contracts, plan operations and systems.
Skill in
Writing programming code to process data including SQL and other tools such as R or Python.
Researching, compiling and analyzing complex data, including querying a claim data warehouse.
Managing projects, including planning, organizing, and prioritizing work assignments to manage a high-volume workload in a fast-paced and changing environment.
Interpreting and applying complex laws, regulations, policies, and procedures.
Completing detailed work with a high degree of accuracy.
Military Occupational Specialty (MOS) Codes

Veterans, Reservists or Guardsmen with experience in the Military Occupational Specialty ( http://www.hr.sao.texas.gov/Compensation/MilitaryCrosswalk/MOSC_AdministrativeSupport.pdf ) along with the minimum qualifications listed above may meet the minimum requirements and are highly encouraged to apply. Please contact Talent Acquisition at careers@trs.texas.gov with questions or for additional information.
To view all job vacancies, visit www.trs.texas.gov/careers or www.trs.csod.com/careersite .

560,2023-07-21,Senior Data Analyst,IL,"You have a clear vision of where your career can go. And we have the leadership to help you get there. At CNA, we strive to create a culture in which people know they matter and are part of something important, ensuring the abilities of all employees are used to their fullest potential.

CNA seeks to offer a comprehensive and competitive benefits package to our employees that helps them — and their family members — achieve their physical, financial, emotional and social wellbeing goals.
For a detailed look at CNA’s benefits, check out our Candidate’s Guide.

Join CNA’s industry-leading Long Term Care team and have an outsized impact managing the finances and operations on the Actuarial Data & Architecture team. With tenured enterprise support, this team leads a multi-year cloud migration strategy to lay the foundation for the adoption of AI tools in CNA’s value chain. As a Senior Data Analyst, you will play a critical role as an Actuarial partner to IT and Data and Analytics teams to drive actuarial modernization, evolve data-driven assumption setting with AI/ML, and bridge technical expertise with the operational expertise of areas such as Claims and Finance. A successful candidate will have strong communication skills, experience with data tools and SQL, an interest in insurance and AI, and the ability to develop business acumen.
JOB DESCRIPTION:
Essential Duties & Responsibilities
Performs a combination of duties in accordance with departmental guidelines:
Collaborates with leadership and subject matter advisors to understand business issues, troubleshoot problems and develop and recommend cost-effective data solutions for data anomalies.
Analyzes data requirements using data manipulation tools (Alteryx, BigQuery, etc.), develops process specifications, and implements data transformation processes within applications.

Drafts high level design of data architecture solutions. Consults with client and application areas to analyze table usage and capabilities, identify associated risks, resolve problems, optimize process performance, and recommend and/or execute resolutions.

Performs data analysis and parallel testing to manage change where appropriate. Executes requisite changes to implement approved requests, ensuring that new functions & data values meet reporting needs.

Defines and promotes aligned data standards & coding best practices. Works with business partners to extract & socialize deep knowledge of CNA’s products and services, regulatory, financial, and internal management information reporting requirements.

Partners with Data & Analytics teams to explore applications of new tools, determine potential functionality and best practices, and implement enhancements with data pipelines (e.g. utilizing ML in assumption setting).

Works with enterprise IT, Infrastructure, Architecture, and Data Delivery teams to deploy cloud solutions (Google VertexAI, Microsoft365, Sharepoint, Alation, LucidChart, etc.). Drives adoption and engagement with solutions upon ensuring cloud solutions meet Long Term Care business requirements.
Identifies and investigates data anomalies, performs root cause analysis, develops solution specifications, and escalates issues as appropriate.
Provides input to data architecture and analysis discussions and decisions on request.
May perform additional duties as assigned.
Reporting Relationship
Typically reports to Director or above
Skills, Knowledge & Abilities
Solid analytical and problem-solving skills.
Solid communication and interpersonal skills to work effectively among all levels of internal/external business partners.
Strong knowledge in at least one data management environment such as Alteryx, BigQuery, Pandas (python) or similar.
Working knowledge of basic data manipulation concepts (joins, data filtering, data cleaning).
Ability to conceptualize how data could fit together to solve a business issue
column2: ability to design solutions with the ‘big picture’ in mind.

column1: Ability to multitask in a fast-paced dynamic workforce.
Agile self-starter. Ability to work independently, as well as in a team. Manage time and resources against competing priorities to accomplish tasks and meet deadlines.
Skillful at learning new system applications/functions.
Readily adapts to change.
Education & Experience
Bachelors’ degree in Actuarial Science, Mathematics, Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, Statistics, Information Technology or related field.

Typically, a minimum of four years’ experience in actuarial, business analysis, data management, financial analysis, accounting, business intelligence, or data science. Data-related project management experience preferred.
Experience/proficiency with ETL or SQL (any dialect) required. Proficiency in Python, R, and/or Linux terminal is preferred, but not required.
Certification with a major cloud platform provider is a plus (e.g. AWS, GCP, Azure, or Snowflake).

Internal CNA employees with data management exposure in areas such as data and analytics, data management, actuarial, IT, finance, accounting, claims, underwriting, etc. are welcome to apply and will be considered.

CNA is committed to providing reasonable accommodations to qualified individuals with disabilities in the recruitment process. To request an accommodation, please contact leaveadministration@cna.com.",Mid-Senior level,1,0,0,0,0,1,1,0,0,1,0

564,2023-07-22,Data Analyst (530344),CA,"Description
Job Summary

Under the general supervision of the Executive Director for Institutional Research and working collaboratively within the IR Team and with Teams from other units, the Associate, Academic and Institutional Studies II (Data Analyst) undertakes studies of considerable scope and complexity including recognizing side issues or related problems for further inquiry and for recommending lines of approach to incorporate them into the main study or to pursue them through a separate project. Long-range and continuing studies are reported periodically and changes in direction or focus, as required by changing circumstances, are cleared with the supervisor. In addition, the incumbent provides support to the different functions of IR as needed.

Institutional Research focuses on providing decision support in areas related to planning, policy development, and institutional effectiveness, among other and generally addresses mandated reporting, data and research requests, and external surveys. Conducting analytical studies may include determining project methods and design, data collection, web-based surveys, an emphasis on quantitative data analysis, interpreting and drawing conclusions from the findings and preparing presentations and other materials to disseminate the findings in such a way that they will be useful for decision-making and institutional improvement.
This position may be eligible to be remote according to Cal Poly’s Telecommuting and Remote Work Guidelines.
Department Summary

The scope of Institutional Research (IR) includes establishing baseline data, fulfilling mandated reporting, preparing analytical reports, and supplying data and analysis to support decision making and University planning. IR, as an interpretive and analytical user of data, works collaboratively with other campus units for data accuracy. The analytical component involves designing, developing, and completing interpretative studies as well as the timely provision of accurate, current, and relevant institutional data to the Cal Poly campus community, the California State University system, and other interested parties.
Key Qualifications
Working knowledge of data warehouse systems, data programming, and data management.
Demonstrated skills in analyzing large complex databases. Ability to independently identify and resolve data conflicts.
Demonstrated ability to use database query languages and tools to retrieve, examine, evaluate, combine, and manipulate data from multiple sources.
Experience with version control and unit testing.

Ability to obtain necessary information for different projects as requested, ability to analyze the information, draw conclusions and develop recommendations, prepare written reports, and lead meetings and negotiations.
Education And Experience

Bachelor’s Degree from a four-year college or university in a field or discipline that included emphasis on research methods and statistical or quantitative analysis. Four years of progressively responsible administrative, technical, or professional analytical experience which demonstrates ability to conduct statistical studies of problems and issues in assigned areas OR the rank of Associate Professor or higher in a four-year college or university and demonstrated experience in research or special study work may substitute for the four years of experience.
Salary And Benefits
Anticipated Hiring Range: $72,000 - $89,000 per year
Classification Range: $68,376 - $123,708 per year

Cal Poly offers a best-in-class benefits program, including health, dental and vision insurance, retirement participation in the Public Employees' Retirement System, and educational benefits for eligible employees. See our benefits website for additional information.
Cal Poly

Cal Poly is a nationally-ranked public university located in San Luis Obispo, California, and known for its Learn by Doing philosophy. Each year more than 20,000 top-tier students come to San Luis Obispo to put knowledge into action, taking their learning outside the classroom as they prepare for careers in engineering, agriculture, science, business, humanities and the built environment. Cal Poly’s hands-on philosophy, small class sizes and close student-faculty mentorships result in graduates ready from day one to impact their communities, California and the world. For more information, visit calpoly.edu.
Diversity Statement

At Cal Poly, we believe that cultivating an environment that embraces and promotes diversity is fundamental to the success of our students, our employees and our community. Bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences and value systems fosters the innovative and creative thinking that exemplifies Cal Poly's values of free inquiry, cultural and intellectual diversity, mutual respect, civic engagement, and social and environmental responsibility.
Cal Poly's commitment to diversity informs our efforts in recruitment, hiring and retention. Cal Poly is an equal opportunity employer.
Supplemental Information

CSU requires faculty, staff, and students who are accessing campus facilities to be immunized against COVID-19 or declare a medical or religious exemption from doing so. Any candidates advanced in a currently open search process should be prepared to comply with this requirement. The systemwide policy can be found at https://calstate.policystat.com/policy/9779821/latest/ and questions may be sent to humanresources@calpoly.edu.

Following a conditional offer of employment, a background check (including a criminal records check) must be completed satisfactorily before any candidate may start work with Cal Poly. 571,2023-07-20,Research Data Analyst 2,CA,"The Division of Cardiovascular Medicine is a dynamic and innovative center dedicated to excellence in research, medical education, and clinical care. Our division is driven by over 80 faculty, clinician educators and instructors who are the pillar of strength in the Division's ongoing efforts into the prevention and treatment of cardiovascular disease.

The Computational Arrhythmia Research laboratory works at the intersection of bioengineering, data science and cardiac electrophysiology (heart rhythm disorders). Our goal is to use detailed data from patients to better understand disease mechanisms, particularly for atrial fibrillation and ventricular tachycardia, and use computational models, machine learning and other tools to develop improved diagnostic and treatment tools.

We are currently seeking a highly skilled and motivated Research Data Analyst 2 to join our team. The ideal applicant will have experience in coding in python and other languages in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP) of electronic health records (EHR) data. The Research Data Analyst will use NLP to process and analyze diverse data sources, including de-identified clinical records, for clinically relevant medical issues in patients with heart rhythm disorders. The applicant should be comfortable analyzing detailed data relevant to heart rhythm disorders including ECG and clinical data.

The position will be primarily responsible for analyzing clinical text data. The applicant should be comfortable with data management, cleaning, and statistical analyses. The role requires working independently with guidance from senior members of the research team, and communicating results in code, orally, and in writing to internal and external researchers and stakeholders. The position involves curating new datasets and implementing data management procedures. The successful applicant will train and update other researchers and staff on these procedures. The position requires project management skills for collaborators and assisting in the design and management of new projects.
Duties Include
Prioritize and extract data from a variety of sources such as notes, survey results, medical reports, and laboratory data, and maintain its accuracy and completeness.
Determine additional data collection and reporting requirements.
Design and customize reports based upon data in the database. Oversee and monitor regulatory compliance for utilization of the data.
Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and eliminate root cause for data problems or justify solutions to be implemented by others.
Create complex charts and databases, perform statistical analyses, and develop graphs and tables for publication and presentation.
Serve as a resource for non-routine inquiries such as requests for statistics or surveys.
Test prototype software and participate in approval and release process for new software.
Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.

Prior research experience in medical technology or a clinical research laboratory would be an advantage.
Prior experience of presenting research, and of writing manuscripts will be an advantage.
Education & Experience (required)

Bachelor's degree and three years of relevant experience or combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.
Knowledge, Skills And Abilities (required)
Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.
Excellent writing and analytical skills.
Ability to prioritize workload.

Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.

column1: 589,2023-07-26,Sr. Data Analyst (Finance) - Remote | WFH,WA,"We are currently seeking an experienced Senior Data Analyst to join our dynamic team and be a key player in shaping our analytics initiatives. Take ownership of the complete analytics lifecycle, from understanding business objectives and data exploration to developing automated reporting and visualizations.
Ensure accuracy, integrity, and consistency of financial data by extracting, transforming, and loading (ETL) data from multiple sources.

Stay ahead of the curve by researching and recommending new analytics tools and platforms.

610,2023-07-20,Research Data Analyst 2,CA,"The Division of Cardiovascular Medicine is a dynamic and innovative center dedicated to excellence in research, medical education, and clinical care. Our division is driven by over 80 faculty, clinician educators and instructors who are the pillar of strength in the Division's ongoing efforts into the prevention and treatment of cardiovascular disease.

The Computational Arrhythmia Research laboratory works at the intersection of bioengineering, data science and cardiac electrophysiology (heart rhythm disorders). Our goal is to use detailed data from patients to better understand disease mechanisms, particularly for atrial fibrillation and ventricular tachycardia, and use computational models, machine learning and other tools to develop improved diagnostic and treatment tools.

We are currently seeking a highly skilled and motivated Research Data Analyst 2 to join our team. The ideal applicant will have experience in coding in python and other languages in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP) of electronic health records (EHR) data. The Research Data Analyst will use NLP to process and analyze diverse data sources, including de-identified clinical records, for clinically relevant medical issues in patients with heart rhythm disorders. The applicant should be comfortable analyzing detailed data relevant to heart rhythm disorders including ECG and clinical data.

The position will be primarily responsible for analyzing clinical text data. The applicant should be comfortable with data management, cleaning, and statistical analyses. The role requires working independently with guidance from senior members of the research team, and communicating results in code, orally, and in writing to internal and external researchers and stakeholders. The position involves curating new datasets and implementing data management procedures. The successful applicant will train and update other researchers and staff on these procedures. The position requires project management skills for collaborators and assisting in the design and management of new projects.

Prioritize and extract data from a variety of sources such as notes, survey results, medical reports, and laboratory data, and maintain its accuracy and completeness.

Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and eliminate root cause for data problems or justify solutions to be implemented by others.

Test prototype software and participate in approval and release process for new software.

The Education Data Services Office is responsible for the collection, quality, analysis and reporting of data submitted to the ESE by public school districts, educational collaboratives and private schools in the Commonwealth. The Education Data Services Office seeks a dynamic, data minded individual to perform the following duties:
Analyze PK-12 data and indicators to inform Department of Elementary and Secondary Education policy decisions.
Produce data and reports for the legislature, governor’s office, media, school districts, and the general public.
Manage data files and prepare and submit required EDEN data to the U.S. Department of Education.
Prepare reports to present to external and internal stakeholders.

Perform other related duties as required.

Commitment to racial equity, combating implicit bias, and cultural competency in the context of the educational system.

Make Your Impact Within a Rapidly Growing Fintech Company

622,2023-07-28,"Senior Data Analyst, Product Operations (Minneapolis, MN)",MN,"Department: Product & Design
Employment Type: Full Time
Location: Minneapolis, MN
Reporting To: Joan Soskin
Description

﻿﻿We're SmartThings, one of the leading IoT ecosystems in the world, creating the most effortless way for anyone to create a smart home. As an independent subsidiary of Samsung, our corporate offices are based in Minneapolis, the Bay Area, and remote home offices throughout the US.

More than 270 million people worldwide use SmartThings to control and manage their connected life. SmartThings delivers simple, powerful experiences across Samsung's leading portfolio of phones, TVs, and appliances. We offer the most versatile smart home experience as an open platform with a rich partner ecosystem. As a founding member of Matter, we are a leader in the industry to help make smart homes more secure, reliable and seamless to use.

SmartThings' culture is built around our core values, offering singular opportunities to make a real, immediate impact in every role. With our focus on trusted ownership, connected leadership, and radical empathy, we embrace inclusive practices and celebrate everyone's uniqueness on our team.

Like the smartphone revolution, smart home technology is transforming the way we interact with the world around us. With SmartThings products, we're reducing global emissions, improving service industries, and creating a safer, smarter planet. Come be a part of the transformation with us! Do the SmartThings!
About The Team

SmartThings is seeking a Senior Data Analyst to join our Product Operations team. Collaborating closely with leaders across the organization, you will play a pivotal role in establishing and leading new data analytics initiatives at SmartThings. You will be responsible for leveraging data to gain valuable insights, power data-driven decision-making, and enhance the overall performance and user experience of our smart home solutions. This is a unique opportunity to shape the future of SmartThings through analytics and drive innovation in the IoT domain.
Key Responsibilities
Collaborate with Samsung's Big Data Center and other global data teams to power our product decisions by enhancing existing datasets, reporting, and dashboards.

Act as a data-driven thought partner to our Product Managers and Product leadership team. Educate our teams to help us ask better questions, interpret findings more effectively, and drive informed decision making.
Develop or enhance self-service data tools to power insight, discovery, and communication. Conduct individual analyses when needed to drive business objectives, and facilitate training.

Build and execute on a roadmap for data enhancements to align with SmartThings' product vision and business objectives. Understand and communicate the building blocks needed, identify any gaps, and drive progress toward best-in-class practices.

Support data collection, governance, and compliance initiatives in partnership with teams across SmartThings globally. Identify and collect relevant data from different sources, ensuring data accuracy and completeness. Partner with global security teams to ensure compliance with data privacy regulations and data governance policies while handling sensitive information and conducting analyses.
Provide technical leadership by staying up-to-date with industry best practices, trends, and emerging technologies to continuously improve our approach.
Skills Knowledge And Expertise
Inclusive Hiring Practices

Our hiring team is passionate about diversity, equity and inclusion, and the data shows that candidates from underrepresented groups are less likely than others to apply for a career opportunity if their qualifications and experience don't appear to be an identical match. We welcome candidates from every professional background, so even if you aren't certain you meet every requirement, we encourage you to apply!
What You Bring On Day One (Required Qualifications)
Proficiency in data analysis tools/programming languages such as Python, R, SQL, or similar, and experience with data visualization
Strong analytical mindset, customer orientation, and curiosity
Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively with diverse teams and stakeholders around the globe
Ability to shift effectively between detail-oriented work and big-picture thinking
5+ years of experience in data analytics, or similar role
Bachelor's or Master's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or a related field, or equivalent experience.
Desired Skills
Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Superset, Power BI, Tableau)
Passion for IoT and smart home technologies, with a desire to contribute to an industry-leading company.
Knowledge of Korean language
International business and organizational experience
SmartThings Benefits
Why You'll Love Working at SmartThings

You'll receive a competitive compensation package and comprehensive health benefits (medical, dental, vision, HSA with employer contribution, life & disability insurance, a competitive 401(k) with a 5% employer match, and more)
You'll have access to generous paid leave for parents, including 8 weeks Parental Leave and 8 more weeks for Childbirth Recovery Leave paid at 100%
You'll enjoy work/life flexibility through our unlimited PTO plan, Summer Fridays, 12 paid holidays each year, and an emphasis on work/life balance.

Our commitment to diversity, equity, inclusion and belonging is embedded into our culture and our work, and you'll have opportunities to join forums and groups and participate in our ongoing projects.
We are a group of bright, kind, and goal-oriented people. You can be your authentic self here, and are empowered to encourage others to do the same!
We are a successful, fast-growing company at the forefront of IoT.
We are a technologically and data-driven business.
We are committed to our customers and developers.
We love solving problems, thinking creatively, and trying new things.
We believe in autonomy & taking initiative.
We take what we do seriously–we don't take ourselves seriously.
We have a smart, experienced leadership team that wants to do it right and is open to new ideas.

Do you desire to be part of a hardworking, dynamic IT operations team that is passionate about helping people solve IT problems?

We are ranked as one of Computerworld 's Top Places to Work in IT 5 years running, and we are seeking a IT Data Analyst to join our Desktop Services Group. As an IT Data Analyst, you will be responsible for analyzing, developing and engineering reports that support data-driven decision making throughout the department. You will work closely with department management to deliver analytical insights, which drive operational initiatives.
As an IT Data Analyst ...
Your main responsibility will be to use tools such as PowerBI, ServiceNow, Excel, SQL, Denodo and Splunk to develop dashboards to highlight key performance indicators.

You will prepare documents and presentation materials to include analytics and data findings

You will partner with project team and program management stakeholders to ensure accurate insights are delivered and communicated

Have experience working in IT Operations with an understanding of ITIL processes
Have experience leading an IT support team

Statistical analysis and forecasting: Strong knowledge of statistical methods and techniques, including time series analysis and forecasting, to develop accurate financial models and projections

Machine learning: Experience in applying machine learning algorithms and techniques for forecasting, anomaly detection, and other relevant financial analysis tasks. Familiarity with libraries and frameworks such as scikit-learn or TensorFlow is a plus.

Understanding of serverless architectures and their impact on scalability, cost-efficiency, and data accessibility will be highly beneficial.

Strong problem-solving skills: Proven ability to tackle complex problems, think critically, and provide data-driven solutions and recommendations to optimize financial performance, mitigate risks, and support decision-making processes.

Salary is commensurate with experience.

648,2023-07-26,Business and Data Analyst,VA,"Secure our Nation, Ignite your Future

We provide Scientific, Engineering and Technical Assistance (SETA) support to Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) in Arlington, VA. For sixty years, DARPA has held to a singular and enduring mission: to make pivotal investments in breakthrough technologies for national security.
Being a part of DARPA’s Commercial Strategy Team

DARPA has a 65-year track record of bringing some off the most top technical innovations to the world – the internet, GPS, self-driving cars, LEDs, etc. DARPA has a ~$4.2B annual budget, with less than 200 federal program managers and staff, spread over 6 tech offices. In your role, you will be part of an elite team, working with some of the most brilliant DARPA PMs, DARPA performers, as well as world class commercial advisors, venture, and private investors, on behalf of the Director’s Office, to accelerate the commercialization of some of the most important DARPA technologies to advance DARPA’s mission - to pose and prevent technological surprise.
In this Role you Will

In the role of Business and Data Analyst, you will be working as part of an exciting team, to provide business and data analysis and visualization in a demanding, fast-paced professional services environment. The primary goals are to leverage the Agency’s leadership team’s time to make informed decisions, track and measure performance, benchmark, and provide the visualizations (dashboards) for analysis, portfolio management, and, support the broader team, and successfully serve the Agency’s Mission. You have a deep commitment to advance national and economic security.
Role Highlights

649,2023-07-24,Research Assistant and Data Analyst,CA,"Division of Prevention Science (DPS)
Full Time
Job Summary

This Research Assistant and Data Analyst will support a randomized controlled trial about the provision of guaranteed income (GI) and additional financial supports for low-income Black young adults (age 18-24) in San Francisco and Oakland. Envisioning a more equitable and healthy future requires bold interventions to address poverty, racism, the chronic stress built from poverty and racism, and the fundamental impacts on health. GI represents not only an opportunity to provide for basic needs while youth finish schooling or training programs, but also helps set a course for establishing a career at a critical time in development. Specifically, this trial will evaluate the impacts of GI, financial coaching, and peer learning circles on participants' investment in their future (education, employment training), mental health (depressive symptoms and anxiety), and unmet mental health and sexual/reproductive health service needs.
The employee will apply their knowledge and skills to support study implementation, including: collecting and entering data
column2: contributing to data collection instruments and methods
column3: perform quality control and data cleaning
column4: produce descriptive statistics
column5: assist with study tool development and programming in REDCap
column6: and engaging and retaining participants during the two-year follow-up period. The employee will work closely with the study team, under the supervision of the Project Director, to ensure smooth study implementation, contribute to rigorous data collection and analysis, address and resolve any operational challenges, and maintain strong participant communication and retention over the course of the study.

column1: 650,2023-07-21,Senior Data Analyst,VA,"American College of Radiology (ACR) is a progressive membership organization representing nearly 40,000 medical specialists in radiological care. As a member of our team, you will join a world leader in patient-centered care advocacy, policy and clinical research, quality and safety. Our culture encourages innovation, diversity, integrity and leadership. A nonprofit 501(c)(3), ACR (the American College of Radiology) has over 500 purpose-driven employees in the Greater Washington, DC and Philadelphia region.
If you share our core values of: Leadership • Integrity • Quality • Innovation, we want you on our team!

We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Senior Data Analyst to join our team. As a Senior Data Analyst, you will be responsible for collecting, analyzing, and interpreting large volumes of data about ACR Membership, and using your strong SQL skills to provide valuable insights and support data-driven decision-making.
As a Senior Data Analyst at ACR you will:

Analyze data from various sources, including a data lake and Salesforce, to support the development of reports, and the standardization of reporting templates, dashboards and guidelines to streamline workflows.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business requirements and translate them into analytical solutions.
Present findings and insights to stakeholders – including senior management – in a clear and concise manner, both orally and in written reports.
Identify opportunities for process improvement and recommend data-driven strategies to optimize business performance.
Monitor and track key performance indicators to provide regular updates and insights to stakeholders.
Qualified candidates should possess the following:
Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field such as Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or Computer Science.
7+ years’ work experience as a Data Analyst or Reporting Analyst, with a focus on data extraction, data mapping and reporting.

3+ years of SQL programming experience, including complex queries, stored procedures, views, materialized views, and functions. Experience working AWS Redshift, AWS Athena and MS SQL SERVER is highly desirable.
1+ years of Salesforce Data analytics experience. Should have good understanding of Salesforce objects and experience working with SoQL.
Experience with Association Management System data (especially Salesforce-based systems), or working in membership-based organizations, is highly desirable.
Proficiency in query optimization techniques and performance tuning.
Familiarity with inner joins, outer joins (left join, right join), and cross joins.
Experience with Common Table Expressions and view creation.
Understanding of database design principles and normalization.

Solid understanding of statistical concepts and data analysis techniques. The ability to apply statistical methods and predictive modeling techniques to identify patterns, trends, and correlations within the data is highly desirable.
Collaborate with stakeholders and IT to ensure high-quality communication and results.
Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment, across multiple projects at once, and in a remote-first setting.
Excellent communication and presentation skills, and a solution-oriented mindset

The Mid-Atlantic Permanente Medical Group, (MAPMG) is one of the nation's premier multispecialty medical groups and is the largest integrated medical group in Maryland, Virginia and the District of Columbia. Founded in 1980, the medical group has more than 1,700 Permanente physicians spanning more than 50 subspecialties. Together, we serve approximately 800,000 Kaiser Permanente members in Maryland, Virginia, and the District of Columbia at 34 area medical centers, plus several community hospitals and skilled nursing facilities.
Job Summary:

MAPMG is seeking a Senior Data Analyst to provide analytical and consulting support to MAPMG Leadership in making strategic decisions by analyzing, manipulating, tracking, internally managing and reporting data. This may entail working with our data systems to pull information using SQL, analyzing the information in Excel or other tools, and presenting the data to various leaders around our medical office buildings. Supports and prepares comprehensive analyses, operational and financial reports with written summaries to organizational leadership. To be considered for this opportunity, candidates must reside in Washington DC, Maryland, or Virginia or be willing to relocate. This position offer a hybrid work arrangement with the ability to go into the office twice/week.
Responsibilities:
Work in the medical office buildings with regular physician leadership interaction.
Perform analysis for problem solving and new methodologies by extracting data using tools such as SQL, SAS, MS Access and Excel.
Compile and generate reports from KPHC, Clarity, and workforce management data systems.
Perform data analysis and provide consultative and advisory recommendations to service area leaders to support data requirements for strategic operational and financial decisions.
Participate in and/or lead projects of moderate to complex scope as assigned.

Conduct ongoing user education and provides management consultation on the use and interpretation of analyses, reports, methodologies and source data and systems. May develop spreadsheet and database analyses for presentation and analysis of financial reports.
Partner with controller in maintaining the budget system and managing annual department submissions to generate service area overall budget.
Validate budget information against HR systems and KPHC. Participates in the planning and development of service area, departmental and/or functional budgets.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree and experience with a healthcare organization strongly preferred.
Four plus years related experience in analysis.
Working knowledge of EPIC (Clarity) data systems preferred.
Highly proficient in SQL and Python. Experience in SAS preferable.
Proficient in Excel and Tableau
Working knowledge of the design, construction and use of complex relational databases required.
Strong analytical, organizational, and communication skills required.
Strong verbal, written and presentation communication skills.
Strong experience in understanding business partner needs, documenting partner needs, documenting detailed report requirements, and the generation of reporting test cases.
Ability to express complex analytical and technical information to senior management or to audiences with clinical training.
Must be an independent self-starter.
